metadata.title: Cessna 206
aws::graph::propositions: Military Operators of the Cessna 206
Argentine Army operates six T207 aircraft.
Bolivia operates Cessna 206 aircraft.
Bolivian Air Force operates two U206C aircraft.
Bolivian Air Force operates seven TU206G aircraft.
Colombia operates Cessna 206 aircraft.
Chile operates Cessna 206 aircraft.
Chilean Air Force operated the first Cessna 206 (construction number 0001) as FACh 415 between 1974 and 1980.
Chilean Air Force sold the first Cessna 206 to civilian market after 1980.
Costa Rica operates Cessna 206 aircraft.
Public Force of Costa Rica operated at least four U206s from 1985.
Djibouti operates Cessna 206 aircraft.
Djibouti Air Force operates one U206G aircraft.
Dominican Republic operates Cessna 206 aircraft.
Dominican Air Force operates one Cessna 206 aircraft.
Ecuador operates Cessna 206 aircraft.
Ecuadorian Air Force operates Cessna 206 aircraft.
Guatemala operates Cessna 206 aircraft.
Guatemalan Air Force operated at least four U206s from 1968.
Guyana operates Cessna 206 aircraft.
Guyana Defence Force operates Cessna 206 aircraft.
India operates Cessna 206 aircraft.
Israel operates Cessna 206 aircraft.
Israeli Air Force operates Cessna 206 aircraft.
Madagascar operates Cessna 206 aircraft.
Malagasy Air Force received five second-hand Cessna 206s in June 2019.
